The paper deals with the problem of resource management in a wireless VR network, which involves data transmission and tracking data collection. This falls under the domain of networked systems and communication, which is covered by the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also deals with the optimization problem of maximizing the users' successful transmission probability, which falls under the domain of information theory, covered by the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also deals with the management of VR content, which involves multimedia processing, covered by the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also proposes a transfer learning approach, which involves machine learning and control systems, covered by the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of reducing traffic load, which falls under the domain of distributed computing, covered by the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category.
